		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />C, C++, Java, PHP, and numerous other C-family languages make a distinction between bitwise AND (&amp;) and logical AND (&amp;&amp;). Bitwise AND is the operation performed here. Logical AND is "1 if both values are nonzero; otherwise 0". I just rewrote much of that section to get more of the discussion out of the bit chart.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
